50|$|Nipah {{virus and}} <b>Hendra</b> <b>virus</b> {{are closely related}} {{paramyxoviruses}} that emerged from bats during the 1990s to cause deadly outbreaks in humans and domesticated animals. National Institute of Allergy and Infectious Diseases (NIAID)-supported investigators developed vaccines for Nipah and <b>Hendra</b> <b>virus</b> based on the soluble G-glycoproteins of the viruses formulated with adjuvants. Both vaccines {{have been shown to}} induce strong neutralizing antibodies in different laboratory animals.|$|E
