50|$|Flying foxes {{experimentally}} {{infected with}} the <b>Hendra</b> <b>virus</b> develop a viraemia then excrete the virus in their urine, faeces and saliva for approximately one week. Although they excrete active virus during this time {{there is no other}} indication of an illness. Symptoms of <b>Hendra</b> <b>virus</b> infection of humans may be respiratory, including hemorrhage and edema of the lungs, or encephalitic, resulting in meningitis. In horses, infection usually causes pulmonary oedema, congestion and / or neurological signs.|$|E
